{
  "description": "A close-up shot features the scroll and neck of a violin resting on a textured, woven surface, likely a straw or reed mat. The violin's scroll is a dark, rich brown, with finely crafted curves. The neck of the violin is a warm, honey-toned wood, displaying a gentle gradient of color. Four strings run parallel from the bridge (out of frame) towards the scroll. The woven surface creates strong linear patterns of light and shadow, highlighting its texture. The background is out of focus, suggesting a dark wooden surface. The lighting is soft and warm, emphasizing the wood grain and contours of the instrument.",
